{"type":"message","id":"aa90d8eb","parentId":"fd88a3e5","timestamp":"2026-03-19T06:59:27.893Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Session state is empty and there are no active tasks or blockers. The context is at 67%, which is above the 60% threshold but below the critical 85% threshold that triggers automatic session creation. \n\nSince:\n1. Context usage (67%) is above threshold (60%) but below critical (85%)\n2. No active tasks in session-state\n3. Nothing urgent in heartbeat rules\n\nI should keep the user informed but this isn't an emergency. Let me provide a summary and remind that we're approaching the threshold where a session switch would be beneficial.","thinkingSignature":"489667a164f51e15425cf9bbcbc45f38ed39190908d54f70e503c7d10e9fb7eb"},{"type":"text","text":"<final>\n📊 **Context Monitor Alert**\n\n| Metric | Value |\n|--------|-------|\n| Context Usage | **67%** (133,617 / 200,000 tokens) |\n| Threshold | 60% ⚠️ |\n| Critical | 85% |\n\n**Status:** ⚠️ Above threshold, but not yet critical.\n\n**Session State:** No active tasks — session-state.md is clean.\n\n**Recommendation:** Context is getting high. Not urgent yet, but worth noting that when we hit **85%**, the system will automatically create a new session with memory loaded. If you want to proactively start a fresh session before that happens, just let me know.\n\nFor now, continuing normally — nothing urgent needs attention.\n</final>"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":999,"output":268,"cacheRead":37002,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38269,"cost":{"input":0.00029969999999999997,"output":0.0003216,"cacheRead":0.00111006,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00173136}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773903558163}}
